cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new population-based algorithm for solving Distributed Constraint Optimization Problems (DCOPs) using evolutionary optimization. This falls under the domain of AI, specifically optimization algorithms. 
2. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with DCOPs, which are a class of problems that involve multiple agents working together to optimize a common objective. This falls under the domain of multiagent systems. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new mechanism for improving solutions in AED that considers the optimistic approximation of local benefits. This can be seen as a form of learning, as the agents are using past experience to improve their solutions. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - While the paper does not explicitly deal with robotics, the use of evolutionary optimization and multiagent systems has applications in robotics, such as swarm robotics. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with optimization of a system (DCOPs) using a population-based algorithm, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
